[SN]TITLE[SN]
Tsunami anniversary: Poor nations need 'better access' to science, says NI seismologist

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
More than 200,000 people died in the Indian Ocean tsunami on 26 December 2004. They included 155 people from the UK - one man was from Northern Ireland.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
26 December 2014 Last updated at 19:08 GMT
A world-renowned seismologist based in Northern Ireland has said countries are better prepared to deal with such situations now, but he would like to see the latest science being made more accessible to poorer nations.
BBC Newsline's Mervyn Jess reports.
